snippet.textDisplay:
This was Warner Bros idea (in fact, the boss of Warner Bros). When Crisis on Infinite Earths was done filiming, Warner Bros asked if this cameo could happen (which there was still a way) and because most of the film crew was not present VERY HIGH chamce that nothing about this scene could be leaked (the conclusion of the crossover of course is huge factor in this, so this being a surprise is REFRESHING for a change). Grant Gustin got a call regarding this scene so of course he was running like he was earlier than a Kryptonian that is faster than a speeding bullet to get this filmed.

Of all the cameos I feel this is the best one simply because it was not leaked. I wish I could be surprised like this more often. Also, thank you Warner Bros, now I'm excited for Ezra Miller's Flash movie.
